    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1966-11-22T13:25:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1966-11-22T13:25:00-05:00" n="195"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d195">
                <head>195. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in the United
                        Kingdom</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d195fn1">Source: National Archives and Records
                        Administration, RG 59, Records of the Department of State, Central Files,
                        1964–66, PET 6 IRAN. Secret. Repeated to Tehran and Jidda.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>London</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1966-11-22T18:25:00+00:00">November 22, 1966,
                        1825Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4274. Subject: Iranian Oil. During conversations in London yesterday, Under
                    Secretary <persName>Rostow</persName> stressed importance our parallel efforts
                    to ensure success of oil talks this week in Iran.<note n="2" xml:id="d195fn2">On
                        November 26 Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_MAH1">Meyer</persName> reported
                        in telegram 2298 from Tehran that the Consortium team had tentatively
                        completed its negotiations with the Iranians. (Ibid., PET 6 IRAN)</note>
                    While we did not get as far as British Government did with oil companies, we had
                    made clear both to <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> and to American oil
                    companies our sense of the sensitivity of situation and our hope they would
                    reach a reasonable compromise acknowledging the rightful interests of both
                    sides. FonMin Brown urged separate American approach to <gloss
                        target="#t_ARAMCO1">Aramco</gloss> with respect both to present negotiations
                    and possible future <gloss target="#t_ARAMCO1">Aramco</gloss> transactions with
                    Saudi Arabia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_BDKE1">Bruce</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
